{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01G2feSVMFXcfPPdyg45Tk87","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"ingress-nginx v1.14.1. In this version, there's stricter annotation risk level control. Let me check what annotations are available and whether I need to update the ConfigMap to allow the snippet.\n\nActually, the issue is that the admission webhook checks the risk level. The ConfigMap has `allow-snippet-annotations: \"true\"` but I might need to also set `annotations-risk-level: Critical`.\n\nAlternatively, I can use the standard `limit-rpm` annotation which is a first-class ingress-nginx annotation and doesn't require snippet access.\n\nLet me try:\n1. `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/limit-rpm: \"20\"` - standard rate limiting annotation\n2. `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/limit-burst-multiplier: \"1\"` - to minimize burst\n\nThese are official ingress-nginx annotations and should pass the admission webhook without needing snippet access. The `limit-rpm` annotation creates its own per-ingress zone, which achieves the same rate limiting effect as the global zone defined in the ConfigMap.\n\nThe ConfigMap settings like `limit-req-status-code: \"429\"` will apply to the rate-limiting directive, and `allow-snippet-annotations: \"true\"` enables snippet support. I'll go with `limit-rpm: 20` and test it out.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":812,"cache_read_input_tokens":50743,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":812},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ce9c526c-cd90-4d01-b4f3-4021b236b79d","uuid":"1e62fcb0-f463-4430-8a9c-911740ea00d4","request_id":"req_011CcRN2mHoNFTNMYv2LTUkX"}
